OpenHarmony QEMU ARM Linux-6.6 Watchdog Compatibility Patch

This patch adds the missing `watchdog_en` per-cpu variable that is
required by the OpenHarmony modified watchdog_enable() function.

Root cause: The Linux-6.6 upstream code removed the watchdog_en variable
but OpenHarmony HDF and other components still depend on it.

TODO: This should be replaced with a proper HDF adapter layer to avoid
modifying core kernel code.

diff --git a/kernel/watchdog.c b/kernel/watchdog.c
index 12345678..abcdef00 100644
--- a/kernel/watchdog.c
+++ b/kernel/watchdog.c
@@ -425,6 +425,7 @@ static DEFINE_PER_CPU(struct completion, softlockup_completion);
 static DEFINE_PER_CPU(struct cpu_stop_work, softlockup_stop_work);
+static DEFINE_PER_CPU(unsigned int, watchdog_en);

